CatDescriptText: image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 9, 1960, pg. A9, reads: "Marlene Franklin wears a Laroche coat of T...slan and ...in the full rounded silhouette now making its bow in Paris. It is a white tweed with black flocks."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Marlene Harris Franklin wearing light colored flecked coat with empire waist, wide three quarter length sleeves, and dark gloves, standing in interior of the New Arena Supper Club for the D.I.'s National Foundation benefit
